INSERT INTO `notes` (`id`, `bugid`, `writer`, `time`, `note`) VALUES (286, 161, 666, 1019387024, 'If you have the message boards open in both browsers\r\nsimultaneously, you\\\'re going to hit problems. When you log in,\r\na \\&quot;key\\&quot; is assigned to you and saved as a cookie in your \r\nbrowser. The key is then compared against the saved copy of the\r\nkey in the database, and if they don\\\'t match, you\\\'re\r\nautomatically logged out.\r\n\r\nThe reason for this is because, without this, it would be\r\npossible to spoof a login cookie and pretend to be someone\r\nelse when posting, and get any access they may have, and so\r\non. This is obviously not good.\r\n\r\nNow, when you log in, it should unset any existing login_key\r\ncookie and set a new one with a new key. If you then go to\r\nanother browser, an old key may be used, and you get logged\r\nout again.\r\n\r\nI could change it so that you only ever get one key which can\r\nbe used across browsers, but I\\\'m not fond of this idea, as it\r\nreduces security a bit.\r\n\r\nThe only other thing I can think of is that you\\\'ve disabled\r\ncookies in your browsers. The message boards won\\\'t work\r\nwithout cookies. Period.\r\n\r\nI\\\'m marking this works for me, for the simple reason that it\r\ndoes, both in IE 5 and Mozilla 1.0 RC 1. I\\\'ll install Opera 6\r\nagain shortly and test it in that, but my suspicion remains\r\nthat it\\\'s either because you\\\'re using it in both browsers\r\nsimultaneously, or because cookies are switched off.');
