INSERT INTO `notes` (`id`, `bugid`, `writer`, `time`, `note`) VALUES (459, 103, 94, 1028081774, 'Quoting Request posted by Korathen on Holonet Redesign Topic\non Message Board:\r\n\r\n--\r\n\r\n Pardon me for interrupting your long derailed conversation.\nHowever, I would like to make a request of those who are\ntrying to make site designs for the holonet. As I try to\nsearch for good characters to make profiles of for the NPC\nContest, I am running into one rate-limiting factor\nrepeatedly: the difficulty of finding criminals that meet\ncertain criterion.\r\n\r\nNow, the options to divide by Status have been tremendously\nhelpful in my work so far. However, I think that what would\nbe even more helpful is a larger search engine. Say, the\nability to search by species or skill. Or even the ability\nto search for several factors all at once. That way, suppose\nI need a villan for a run-on who conforms to X type of\ncharacter. Perhaps Y-type species is commonly cast as this X\ntype of character. But because he is the active villan, he\ncannot be dead. Therefore, rather than a half an hour of\nsearching, I could simply go to the Holonet and\ncross-reference Y-type species, with an Active Status, and\nget a full list to choose from.\r\n\r\nDo the rest of you think this is worthwhile. ');
